                <h2 data-uuid="5b8e07ce83264efdb56e0ac308c3efbb"> Document-Based Investigation</h2>
            </div>
            <h3 data-uuid="b36d7fe1bcff4fe78164f36ffe6d3fa5">Part 2: Write an Argument</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="41f6e2e855214641af4ebf6d25845bba">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="958a573a83d14857adaf682eece269fa">Historians still argue about the success of Reconstruction. On one hand, the
                government did achieve its most important goal—the reunification of the nation.
                On the other hand, despite significant progress, Reconstruction failed to secure equal rights for African Americans.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="4d61a58078054165ad8322e780b66e08">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="b60eaa27029b4d2ba4942e5484bc213a"><span>Reconstruction resulted in three constitutional amendments and government efforts such as the Freedmen’s Bureau to promote equal rights in the South. This era, however, also witnessed a determined southern campaign to block racial equality. Write
                an argument in which you support a claim about the impact Reconstruction had on
                African Americans.</span></p>
            <p data-uuid="c45b1702698c4c3aafc6066480c55910">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="b1a21740c12947e7af5ef97eef025f28">
                <li data-uuid="25c901970d494d53ac52bd9f87d0a2bb">
                    Review your notes and sources before you start writing.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="4f916e8381f84df89a61e33eede9b9cb">
                    Use at least <i>two</i> of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic
                    with relevant, well-chosen text evidence from the documents.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="6499a68a1e634089888c5b83b397eff4">
                    Cite specific text evidence from each of the sources in your
                    response.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="d9692fb98e234aea8b0d47ba51ef687a">
                    Plan your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a concluding paragraph.</li>
                <li data-uuid="60f2a9ab164446d0b34f9007ded0dcd6">
                    <p data-uuid="b71b30148cf440be98ef1d0e2400d1e8">Clearly state your claim, or position on the topic, and
                        consider any opposing claims.</p>
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="9d0e87427ded493f8b716f7d50660ac3">
                    <p data-uuid="a864d67e418e4994a235a7d8d7e98d55">Organize your essay in a clear and logical way and use
                        linking words and phrases to clarify the relationship between claims and
                        counterclaims, as well as between ideas.</p>
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="c47c67fad6724b4c972a5c4b9b3d8f33">
                    <p data-uuid="af90f137c56f4b7d8f013b4946728f76">Support your claim with logical reasoning and evidence from
                        credible sources.</p>
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="762072913e6d40afbbf45277d46b8229">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and
                    supports the argument you present.<br />
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
